rb","gloss":"to diffuse, to forspread (said of odors as of blood)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to endow with (with double accusative or with accusative and بِ)","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"ناولني عامل الخدمة ربطة قات شامي فاخرة، وعروسة سجائر. لاحظت أنّ عين النادل كانت تلاحق عروسة السجائر، أمرته أن ينتظر، أزلت غشاءها النايلوني الرقيق ونفحته علبة، فانصرف مسروراً.","english":"A service worker brought me a bundle of fine Levantine qāt, and a carton of cigarettes. I recognized that the eye of the waiter was fixed on the carton of cigarettes, I hight him to bide, removed the thin nylon covering and tipped him a packet, and he left in gaiety."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَفَحَ (nafaḥa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ن ف ح (n f ḥ). Also compare نَفَخَ (nafaḵa) and فَاحَ (fāḥa)."},"ipa":null}